The paper discusses learning-based control for robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of machine learning techniques such as Gaussian processes (GP) and model predictive control (MPC) suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on safety and adaptation in changing operating conditions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV), as vision is used for localization in the experiments.
